        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 26 at 7:04PM CDT until May 26 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Armstrong County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Carson County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northwestern Donley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 800 PM CDT.

* At 704 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Groom, or 15 miles east of Panhandle, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Lake Mcclellan and Groom.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
